      "body" : "i never understood why there are people who call some parts of some API &quot;dead&quot; or &quot;legacy&quot; just because it might be inefficient. NEWSFLASH : almost all algorithms out there can be optimized, quite a lot are inefficient - yet noone calls it &quot;dead&quot;. Efficiency isnt important anymore, we are in the 21st century so unless you&#39;re writing high-performance embedded software for space-shuttles (well, the successor) there is no point in ranting against API like that -- and even then : <i>software engineers</i> simply choose some alternative, they dont rant but dont worry about that just yet :)"
