      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@specializt: I think it&#39;s entirely reasonable to call it a legacy API if there&#39;s an alternative which is clearly better in most situations. Not only is <code>Vector</code> less efficient in terms of synchronizing unnecessarily, but by doing that synchronization it can give the <i>illusion</i> of being thread-safe to users who are new to threading and think that synchronizing each operation is sufficient to make it safe to use arbitrarily across threads. I&#39;m still very happy to recommend moving from <code>Vector</code> to <code>ArrayList</code> in almost all cases."
