      "body" : "@specializt: Nope, I don&#39;t think so. Searching for &quot;define:legacy&quot;, the relevant adjective for computing states: &quot;denoting or relating to software or hardware that has been superseded but is difficult to replace because of its wide use.&quot; That sounds pretty similar to what I said. Note that &quot;better in most situations&quot; is a pretty high bar - while <code>LinkedList&lt;T&gt;</code> is better than <code>ArrayList&lt;T&gt;</code> in <i>some</i> situations, the reverse is often true - neither effectively deprecates the other."
