      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@dhardy List with an array as its underlying implementation. There&#39;s <code>ArrayList</code>, <code>LinkedList</code>, etc., all of which implement the interface <code>List</code>, so if you want to utilize the <code>List</code> methods without having to know what the underlying implementation actually is you can just take a <code>List</code> as a parameter to methods, etc. The same applies for implementers of <code>Map</code> and so on. Meanwhile, C++ does have a <code>std::array</code> class, which is just a template-based replacement for C-style static length arrays."
